Let $x_n, y_n in RR$. Show that if both $sum_(n=1)^oo x_n$ and $sum_(n=1)^oo
y_n$ converge then $sum_(n=1)^oo x_n + y_n$ converges

Suppose $sum_(n=1)^oo x_n + y_n = oo$. We can split the sum into two sums
$sum_(n=1)^oo x_n + sum_(n=1)^oo y_n = oo$. But both of these converge. Thus
$sum_(n=1)^oo x_n + sum_(n=1)^oo y_n < oo$. 

